@startuml flow_command_execution
!theme plain
title Command Submission & Execution Flow

actor "User / UI" as user
participant "ClientHandle" as handle
participant "mpsc channel" as chan
participant "Command\nForwarder Task" as fwd
participant "WorkQueue" as wq
participant "Event Loop\n(main)" as loop
participant "CommandAction\n(concrete cmd)" as cmd
participant "ServerState" as state
participant "Outbound\nChannel" as outbound
participant "TcpWriter\nTask" as writer
database "Mumble Server" as server

== 1. Command Submission ==

user -> handle : handle.send(JoinChannel { channel_id: 3 })
handle -> chan : cmd_tx.send(Box::new(JoinChannel { .. }))
chan -> fwd : ext_cmd_rx.recv()
fwd -> wq : wq_sender.send_command(cmd)

== 2. Command Dispatch ==

wq -> loop : WorkItem::UserCommand(cmd)
loop -> cmd : cmd.execute(&state)

note right of cmd
    JoinChannel::execute(&self, state):
      session = state.own_session()   // e.g. 42
      return CommandOutput {
          tcp_messages: vec![
              UserState { session: 42, channel_id: 3 }
          ],
          udp_messages: vec![],
          disconnect: false,
      }
end note

cmd -> state : read: own_session() → 42
state --> cmd : Some(42)
cmd --> loop : CommandOutput

== 3. Output Processing ==

loop -> outbound : send(UserState { session: 42, channel_id: 3 })
outbound -> writer : ControlMessage::UserState(...)
writer -> server : [type=9][len][UserState protobuf]

note over loop
    If output.disconnect == true,
    the event loop would call
    handler.on_disconnected()
    and break.
end note

== 4. Server Response ==

server -> loop : (via TCP reader → WorkQueue)\nUserState { session: 42, channel_id: 3 }
loop -> state : apply_user_state(...)
loop -> user : handler.on_control_message(UserState)

note over user, server
    The server confirms the channel change
    by echoing back a UserState message.
    ServerState is now updated with the
    user's new channel_id.
end note

@enduml
